                    <h2><?=$title; ?></h2>
                    <p><code class="inline-code">pop-session</code> is a component used to manage sessions and session data in the PHP web environment.
                        It includes the ability to also manage namespaces within the session as well as timed-based and
                        request-based expirations.</p>
                    <p>You can create a session and store and fetch data from it:</p>
                    <pre><code class="language-php">use Pop\Session\Session;

$sess = Session::getInstance();

